dcterms:description: CARLA is an open urban driving simulator that provides a high-fidelity simulation environment for autonomous driving research, allowing for the generation of realistic highway traffic scenarios.
dcterms:title: CARLA

dcterms:creator: M. Treiber
A. Hennecke
D. Helbing
dcterms:description: The Intelligent Driving Model (IDM) is a car-following model that simulates the behavior of vehicles in traffic, focusing on maintaining safe distances and speeds.
dcterms:title: Intelligent Driving Model (IDM)

dcterms:creator: A. Kesting
M. Treiber
D. Helbing
dcterms:description: The Minimizing-Overall-Braking Induced-by-Lane-changes (MOBIL) model is used for generating safe lane change decisions based on the relative positions and velocities of vehicles.
dcterms:title: Minimizing-Overall-Braking Induced-by-Lane-changes (MOBIL)

dcterms:creator: M. Werling
J. Ziegler
S. Kammel
S. Thrun
dcterms:description: The Frenet Frame dataset provides a framework for optimal trajectory generation in dynamic street scenarios, focusing on the representation of vehicle motion in a Frenet coordinate system.
dcterms:title: Frenet Frame

dcterms:description: The Deep Q-Network (DQN) is a reinforcement learning algorithm that enables agents to learn optimal policies through deep learning techniques, particularly in environments with high-dimensional state spaces.
dcterms:title: Deep Q-Network (DQN)
